<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,906,1003]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[276,441,906,931]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Erebaxonopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[276,441,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Erebaxonopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known thus far from one species from Europe, two species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1213,1277,907,930]" name="Japan" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Japan</collectingCountry>
and one from North 
<collectingCountry box="[225,321,942,967]" name="United States of America" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">America</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[337,467,942,967]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" refString="Cook, D. R. (1974) Water mite genera and subgenera. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 21, 1 - 860." type="journal article" year="1974">
Cook 
<number box="[408,467,943,967]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" value="1974.0">1974</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets" box="[479,668,942,967]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" refString="Viets, K. O. (1987) Die Milben des Sußwassers (Hydrachnellae und Halacaridae [part.], Acari). 2: Katalog. Sonderbande des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg, 8, 1 - 1012." type="journal article" year="1987">
K.O. Viets 
<number box="[608,668,943,967]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" value="1987.0">1987</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The record of a new species described below is the first record of the genus from the Oriental region.
</paragraph>
